race.comment: BOSTON LEGAL (8) missed the frame last time when fourth (19.90) at Healesville but prior to that had two placings in a row. Can discover winning form. WHODAT WHISKEY (7) was beaten for speed from wide out but attacked the line strongly to place, 5 lengths from the winner (22.77) at Ballarat in Grade 5. Bold showing expected. CHILL OUT PLATE (1) struggled to get involved last start after missing the jump at Healesville, but prior to that won by a neck at Bendigo (24.13) beating Moraine Piper in a Grade 5 NP on January 20. Has ability and can measure up. SKY SPRINGER (4) can fill a top-three spot.
